[SN]TITLE[SN]
Suspected Hampshire sinkhole closes road

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A one-metre (3ft) wide suspected sinkhole has appeared in a road in Hampshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police have shut part of the westbound A27 Southampton Road in Titchfield after the hole opened up earlier.
Highways officers from Hampshire County Council are also at the scene assessing the damage.
Police said weather had been bad in the area with several reports of flash flooding. One lane westbound is likely to be closed overnight.
